title: For Sale:  Mossberg 535 Combo - 12 Guage - Pump Action - 2 Barrels
postcontent: Hello and thank you for considering my listing!I am looking to sell my Mossberg 535 12 guage pump action shotgun. It is the combo version that comes with the 28" choke barrel and the 24" rifled slug barrel. It is in very good condition and will include all the original accessories such as the choke tubes, choke removal tool, wooden dowel to limit magazine capacity for bird hunting, lock, and the original box as well. This was my very first firearm I purchased, and as a result it has been absolutely babied. It has seen VERY little use, which is also the reason I have decided to sell it.I have decided to sell it along with the custom case/bag I purchased from Bagmaster in St. Louis, MO. It opens like a book and has two pockets on the one side to hold the barrels, and a single larger pocket on the other side to hold the stock/receiver/magazine part of the shotgun. It has a pouch on the front of the case to hold misc. parts/tools/ammo/etc. It is really nice because it is much shorter in length than other cases which are designed for carrying the shotgun with the barrel attached, and it holds both barrels without them banging together.The choke barrel has the standard "rib" system for aiming, and the rifled slug barrel has adjustable sights for aiming. The top of the receiver is drilled and tapped for mounting a scope/red dot sight. This is nice because you can swap the barrels and not have to re-zero the scope. I have not personally mounted any kind of scope, but it could be easily done if you wanted to.I will also include 3 boxes of slugs (15 total slugs), I bought 5 boxes awhile ago and shot 2 of them for fun and then the remaining 3 boxes have just sat around since. So basically the rifled slug barrel has exactly 10 slugs shot through it. I am not sure exactly how many shells the choke barrel has, but I would guess somewhere around 300-400.Now on to the boring legal stuff:1. I will only sell to a person who has a valid FOID card. 2. Per new law, I will have to submit your FOID number to the ISP for validation prior to sale. They will issue an approval number confirming your FOID is valid.3. The 24 hour waiting period will be followed to the second.4. We will complete a comprehensive bill of sale that will include all the required information about buyer, seller, and the shotgun.5. I will accept cash only.Thank you for considering my listing and I look forward to speaking with you! Armslist limits each post to 3 pictures, however I would be happy to send more pictures via email upon request. Please no trade offers, I am looking to sell outright only at this time.- Kevin
